    <div id="text">     
        <h1>The Cover Art Archive</h1>

        <p>
        The Cover Art Archive is a joint project between the <a href="http://archive.org">Internet Archive</a> and 
        <a href="http://musicbrainz.org">MusicBrainz</a>, whose goal is to make cover art images of
        music releases available to everyone on the Internet in an organised and convenient way.
        </p>

        <p>
        If you have the <a href="http://wiki.musicbrainz.org/MBID">MBID</a> of a release you can construct a URL
        to retrieve the cover art for it. To find out more, please see our <a href="http://wiki.musicbrainz.org/Cover_Art_Archive/API">API documentation</a>.
        </p>

        <p>
        The MusicBrainz community curates the collection of images in the archive. MusicBrainz users upload 
        the images to the archive and peer review them to ensure that they are correct, free of spam and
        of the best possible quality. If you want to help improve this collection, see <a href="http://wiki.musicbrainz.org/How_to_Add_Cover_Art">our guide for adding cover art</a> (you'll need to <a href="http://musicbrainz.org/register">create a MusicBrainz account</a> first).
        </p>

        <p>Important notes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Images are uploaded from users' computers directly to Internet Archive servers.</strong></li>
            <li><strong>All images are copyrighted by their respective copyright owners.</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <p>
        If you have any question regarding the images in coverartarchive.org, please email info at archive dot org.
        </p>
        <div id="links">
            <a class="link" href="http://archive.org">Internet Archive</a>
            <a class="link" href="http://musicbrainz.org">MusicBrainz</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

